onship between original and copy, even more so in the medium of film than in the medium of theatre. Dienstag's provocative and stylish essay is debated by an exceptional group of interlocutors comprising Clare Woodford, Tracy B. Strong, Margaret Kohn, Davide Panagia and Thomas Dumm. The volume closes with a robust response from Dienstag to his critics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picturesxPhilosophy. 0aMotion picturesxPlots, themes, etc. 0aMotion picturesxPolitical aspects. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh  aJean D'Alembert.  aJean-Jacques Rousseau.  aStanley Cavell.  acinema.  acontemporary culture.  ademocratic community.  amoral perfectionism.  aphilosophical pessimism.  apolitical life.  aremarriage comedies.1 aDienstag, Joshua Foa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDienstag, Joshua Foa, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDumm, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKohn, Margaret, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPanagia, Davide, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStrong, Tracy B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWoodford, Clare, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packagez978311128282440uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/9781784997359zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781784997359zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781784997359/original